[2026-03-18T11:29:02.070Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MHcDE7XpnQr59cKv2nH787","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011WtfXz8y1eCn2y2GMGgrVH","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"2dfb2d45-bb93-4ef6-99ab-24e0361f0183\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"user_benefit\",\n    \"title\": \"Real-Time Execution Streaming Fabric via SSE\",\n    \"description\": \"Replace the current polling-based execution output retrieval (GET /api/executions/:id with offset parameter, httpApi.ts line 277-282) with a real-time streaming fabric. Clients would open an SSE connection to /api/executions/:id/stream and receive stdout chunks, progress updates, persona events, and completion signals as they happen. The dispatcher already buffers output and forwards to Kafka — the streaming endpoint would tap the same in-memory active execution map plus Kafka consumer for replay. This enables live dashboards showing all active executions across tenants, collaborative monitoring where multiple users watch the same execution, and execution replay from any historical point using persisted output data.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Polling is fundamentally wrong for streaming output — it adds latency, wastes bandwidth, and cannot deliver the real-time experience users expect when watching AI work. The architecture already has all the pieces (in-memory output arrays, Kafka topics for output/progress/lifecycle), but no push delivery to clients. SSE streaming would transform the user experience from refresh-and-wait to watch-it-work, which is the emotional difference between a batch job and a living assistant.\",\n    \"effort\": 6,\n    \"impact\": 8,\n    \"risk\": 4\n  }'","description":"Save idea 4 witho